<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-15T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">548.G1/121: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-15T13:00:00+03:00">May 15, 1943—1
                                p.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received May 15—11:56 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>457. Department’s 230, May 10, 7 p.m., to Kuibyshev. Please clarify what is
                        meant by the separate declaration “similar to the Polish”.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>